A RESOLUTION
1 Urging the Metropolitan Atlanta Rapid Transit Authority to reaffirm its commitment to an
2 extension of the rail system along the east side of Interstate 20 in South DeKalb County; and
3 for other purposes.
4 WHEREAS, residents of South DeKalb County have paid a 1 percent sales tax to fund
5 operations and capital improvements to the Metropolitan Atlanta Rapid Transit Authority
6 (MARTA) since 1972; and
7 WHEREAS, there has been no rail expansion in South DeKalb County while MARTA
8 extended rail stations to Central DeKalb County in 1993 with Indian Creek Station and to
9 North Fulton and North DeKalb counties in 1996 with Buckhead, Medical Center, and
10 Dunwoody Stations and again in 2000 with Sandy Springs and North Springs Stations; and
11 WHEREAS, the 9th and 13th amendments to the Rapid Transit Contract Agreement specify
12 MARTA's priority to extend heavy rail beyond the Indian Creek Station to Stonecrest Mall;
13 and
