14 WHEREAS, in April, 2012, the MARTA board of directors approved a heavy rail extension
15 from the Indian Creek Station to run parallel along Interstate 285 South and continuing east
16 along Interstate 20 to the Stonecrest Mall area as a locally preferred alternative; and
17 WHEREAS, residents of South DeKalb County have limited access to the MARTA rail
18 system; and
19 WHEREAS, extension of the MARTA rail along the south/southeastern corridor of Interstate
20 20 would create opportunities for transit oriented development.
21 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
22 the members of this body express its support of an extension of heavy rail along the east side
23 of Interstate 20 and urge the Metropolitan Atlanta Rapid Transit Authority to reaffirm its
24 commitment to an extension of the rail system in South DeKalb County.
25 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body urge the elected officials from
26 DeKalb County and the CEO and Board of Directors of the Metropolitan Atlanta Rapid
27 Transit Authority to work together in developing a comprehensive mass transit plan for
28 DeKalb County that includes heavy and light rail alternatives to extend the existing rail
29 system from the City of Atlanta to the City of Stonecrest.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
32 CEO and members of the board of directors of the Metropolitan Atlanta Rapid Transit
33 Authority, the CEO of DeKalb County, and members of the DeKalb County Board of
34 Commissioners.
